<setup>

  <selectFromSequence assignNames="k" from="1.5" to="2.5" step="0.25" numToSelect="1"/>  
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="m" from="2" to="5" step="1" numToSelect="1"/>    
  <selectFromSequence assignNames="n" from="3" to="7" step="1" numToSelect="1"/> 
  
  <math name="z" simplify>$n-1</math>

  <function name="s" symbolic="true">$m * $k^x - $n</function>
  <derivative name="sP" symbolic="true">$s</derivative>  


</setup>

  <p>Suppose that <m>s(t) = <math simplify>$$s(t)</math></m> tells us the position (in feet) away from <m>s = 0</m> of an object moving along a straight line at time <m>t</m> (in minutes).  To estimate the instantaneous velocity of the object at <m>t = <math simplify>$z</math></m>, first compute the following average velocities.  Report your results to at least 4 decimal places of accuracy.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p><m>AV_{<math simplify>[$z,$z+0.1]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z+0.1)-$$s($z))/0.1</award></answer></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>AV_{<math simplify>[$z,$z+0.01]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z+0.01)-$$s($z))/0.01</award></answer></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>AV_{<math displayDigits="5" simplify>[$z,$z+0.001]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z+0.001)-$$s($z))/0.001</award></answer></p>
    </li>  
    <li> 
      <p><m>AV_{<math simplify>[$z-0.1,$z]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z)-$$s($z-0.1))/0.1</award></answer></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>AV_{<math simplify>[$z-0.01,$z]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z)-$$s($z-0.01))/0.01</award></answer></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>AV_{<math displayDigits="5" simplify>[$z-0.001,$z]</math>} = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z)-$$s($z-0.001))/0.001</award></answer></p>
    </li>    
  </ul>
<p>Based on these average velocities, a good estimate of the object's instantaneous velocity at <m>t = <math simplify>$z</math></m> is <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award> ($$s($z+0.001)-$$s($z-0.001))/0.002</award></answer>, and the units on the instantaneous velocity are         
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="choice2" inline>
            <choice>feet per hour</choice>
            <choice>feet</choice>
            <choice>feet per second</choice>
            <choice credit="1">feet per minute</choice>
            <choice>minutes</choice>  
          </choiceInput>            
        </answer>. </p>

